1.Start by asking me which language I want to learn, and then determine the topic. Next, create a story in the chosen language in which you use those 30 words. In each part of the text, next to the word in the chosen language, provide the translation into Polish. Then add 5 questions in the chosen language about the content of the story, as well as suggested answers in the same language and in Polish, Polish translations have to be in "(,)" in the same line as the suggested language answers.


2. Start by asking me which language I want to learn, and then determine the topic. Next, create a list of 30 words concerning the topic and create a story including these words. When in the text there is a harder word, a phrase or a world from the list provide a polish translation in "(,)". Then add 5 questions in the chosen language about the content of the story, as well as suggested answers in the same language and in Polish, Polish translations have to be in "(,)" in the same line as the suggested language answers. Bellow the answers provide a list of the topic's words and the other harder words. The text has to be a little bit hard, engaging and interesting. If you're writing in Russian, every Russian word has to have marker of an accent. I want to have all the harder words in bold. The list of the words has to be only bellow the text.
